## CRITICAL NOTES

Zdog dragRotate: always set to false in scene HTML for WVC export.
The WVC headless Chrome has no mouse events so drag doesn't work
and leaving it true causes Zdog to initialize in an unexpected state.
In preview mode (browser), can be true for interactivity.
Use a query param: dragRotate: new URLSearchParams(location.search).has('preview')

Zdog canvas sizing: Zdog's coordinate system is centered.
At zoom=4, a shape at translate: {x:0, y:0} appears at center.
x increases right, y increases DOWN, z increases TOWARD camera.
Inject this into the Zdog system prompt — it's non-obvious.

Component buildFn isolation: each component function must be
completely self-contained. No shared variables between components.
Prefix all internal variables with the component id to prevent collisions.
Function naming: build_{componentId.replace(/-/g,'_')}

Three.js r128 on CDN: verify all geometries used in components
exist in r128. BoxGeometry, SphereGeometry, CylinderGeometry,
TorusGeometry, PlaneGeometry, ConeGeometry, TubeGeometry,
EdgesGeometry, WireframeGeometry all exist.
BufferGeometry exists. CapsuleGeometry does NOT (added r142).

MATERIALS constants must be injected before any scene code runs.
Add them to the Three.js template between the THREE global and
the layer's generatedCode/assembled code.

For the component thumbnail generator: use the same canvas
approach as assets — createCanvas(160, 90) in Node.js with
the canvas npm package, run the build function, capture frame
at t=2 seconds, save as base64.

Zdog text: do NOT use Zfont in generated scenes. It requires
loading a font file which adds complexity and latency. Instead:
use a separate HTML layer on top of the Zdog layer for any text.
The agent should automatically add an HTML layer when the Zdog
scene needs labels or titles.
```